🐍 What is Pandas?

Pandas is a powerful Python library used for:

Data analysis
Data manipulation
Data cleaning
Working with structured data (tables like Excel or SQL)

It is built on top of:

NumPy
🔥 Why Pandas is Important
Handles large datasets easily
Provides fast operations
Works with CSV Excel SQL JSON
Used in Data Science Machine Learning AI
📦 Installation
pip install pandas
📊 Core Data Structures
1. Series (1D)
import pandas as pd

data = pd.Series([10, 20, 30])
print(data)

👉 Output:

0    10
1    20
2    30
2. DataFrame (2D Table)
data = {
    "Name": ["A", "B", "C"],
    "Age": [20, 21, 22]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
print(df)

👉 Output:

  Name  Age
0    A   20
1    B   21
2    C   22
📁 Reading Files
df = pd.read_csv("file.csv")
df = pd.read_excel("file.xlsx")
df = pd.read_json("file.json")
💾 Writing Files
df.to_csv("file.csv")
df.to_excel("file.xlsx")
🔍 Viewing Data
df.head()     # first 5 rows
df.tail()     # last 5 rows
df.info()     # structure
df.describe() # statistics
🎯 Selecting Data
df["Name"]          # column
df.loc[0]           # row by index
df.iloc[0]          # row by position
df[["Name", "Age"]] # multiple columns
🔄 Filtering Data
df[df["Age"] > 20]
➕ Adding Column
df["Salary"] = [1000, 2000, 3000]
❌ Handling Missing Values
df.isnull()
df.dropna()
df.fillna(0)
🔁 Grouping Data
df.groupby("Age").mean()
🔗 Merging Data
pd.merge(df1, df2, on="id")
📈 Sorting Data
df.sort_values("Age")
🧠 Important Functions Summary
Function	Use
head()	First rows
tail()	Last rows
info()	Structure
describe()	Stats
groupby()	Group data
merge()	Combine data
sort_values()	Sorting
⚡ Advantages
Easy syntax
Fast computation
Handles missing data
Works with large datasets
❌ Disadvantages
Uses more memory
Not ideal for extremely large big data (use Spark)
🔗 Where Pandas is Used
Data Science
Machine Learning
Data Cleaning
Financial Analysis
Business Intelligence
🧩 Pandas vs Other Tools
Tool	Use
Pandas	Data analysis
NumPy	Numerical operations
Matplotlib	Visualization
Scikit-learn	ML models
🚀 Simple Real Example
import pandas as pd

df = pd.read_csv("students.csv")

# Filter students with marks > 80
top_students = df[df["Marks"] > 80]

print(top_students)
📌 Pro Tips (Very Important)
Always check data using head()
Clean data before analysis
Use groupby() for insights
Use apply() for custom logic
